Linus and Luke revisit the Chevy Volt and the wild reality that many owners never even plugged them in. Plug-in hybrids were supposed to be the perfect blend of EV and gas car, but poor communication left drivers treating them like regular hybrids. Toyota’s new “Charge Minder” app tries to gamify charging with streaks and reminders, but the question remains: why pay thousands more for a plug-in if you don’t actually use it?

Linus and Luke discuss Google’s announcement that ChromeOS and Android will be combined into a single platform for PCs starting in 2026. With talk of AI integration, Linux app support, and Qualcomm partnerships, the plan sounds ambitious, but can Google actually stick with it? Plus, the guys weigh in on Meta’s bizarre new AI-generated video feed, “Vibes.”
